{"type":"message","id":"50ae86bb","parentId":"319f9ae1","timestamp":"2026-03-24T03:58:26.951Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Let me read the most recent pulse log.","thinkingSignature":"d40b955382637849e2941533c26915d89f981b4c20bbf1dbf0828e4e565360b3"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_xpnfnw9o65xa_1","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\sandbox\\memory\\session\\pulse_2026-03-23 234907.md"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_xpnfnw9o65xa_2","name":"process","arguments":{"action":"poll","sessionId":"young-tidepool","timeout":55000}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":452,"output":106,"cacheRead":11878,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":12436,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774324704265}}
{"type":"message","id":"93082ebc","parentId":"50ae86bb","timestamp":"2026-03-24T03:58:26.959Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_xpnfnw9o65xa_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Pulse: 2026-03-23 234907\n\n## Applied Mutations\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\nRejected: research/tic_experiment.ps1 (missing)\n\n## LLM Response\n<think>\r\nLet me analyze the current state and determine what concrete action to take.\r\n\r\nLooking at the goals, I need to advance Phase 1, specifically the TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) experiment. The next action is:\r\n- Implement TIC classifier on `logs/pulse_*.md` files\r\n- Measure invariant/variant classification accuracy\r\n- Predict next pulse content from invariants\r\n- Validate against success criteria (>70%, >60%)\r\n\r\nSo I need to create a TIC classifier that:\r\n1. Reads pulse log files\r\n2. Classifies content as invariant (persistent across pulses) vs variant (unique to specific pulse)\r\n3. Uses invariants to predict next pulse content\r\n4. Measures accuracy against criteria\r\n\r\nLet me look at what exists:\r\n- `research/COMPRESSION-CAUSAL-DUALITY.md` - the theory doc\r\n- `logs/pulse_*.md` - the actual pulse logs\r\n\r\nI should create a TIC experiment script or implementation. Let me create a Python script that implements the TIC classifier.\r\n\r\nThe key insight is:\r\n- Invariant = content that appears in multiple pulses (causal structure)\r\n- Variant = content unique to a single pulse (noise/ephemeral)\r\n\r\nFor prediction:\r\n- Given current pulse invariants, predict what next pulse invariants will be\r\n- Compare predicted vs actual\r\n\r\nLet me create a concrete implementation.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) experiment is the next critical step to unify Phase 1 and Phase 2. I need to implement a classifier that identifies invariants across pulse logs and uses them to predict subsequent pulse content.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nCreate `experiments/tic/tic_classifier.py` - the core TIC implementation that:\r\n1. Extracts content tokens from pulse logs\r\n2. Classifies each token as invariant (>1 occurrence) or variant (single occurrence)\r\n3. Uses invariant sequences to predict next-pulse invariants\r\n4. Outputs classification and prediction accuracy metrics\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n```\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: #!/usr/bin/env python3\r\n\"\"\"\r\nTIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) Classifier\r\nTests hypothesis: causal structure IS invariant structure.\r\nCompressor that finds invariants has discovered causation.\r\n\"\"\"\r\n\r\nimport os\r\nimport re\r\nfrom collections import defaultdict\r\nfrom pathlib import Path\r\n\r\nclass TICKlassifier:\r\n    def __init__(self, logs_dir=\"logs\"):\r\n        self.logs_dir = Path(logs_dir)\r\n        self.pulses = []  # List of (filename, tokens)\r\n        self.token_frequency = defaultdict(int)\r\n        self.invariant_tokens = set()\r\n        self.variant_tokens = set()\r\n    \r\n    def load_pulses(self):\r\n        \"\"\"Load all pulse_*.md files sorted chronologically.\"\"\"\r\n        pulse_files = sorted(self.logs_dir.glob(\"pulse_*.md\"))\r\n        for pf in pulse_files:\r\n            content = pf.read_text()\r\n            tokens = self._tokenize(content)\r\n            self.pulses.append((pf.name, tokens))\r\n            for t in tokens:\r\n                self.token_frequency[t] += 1\r\n    \r\n    def _tokenize(self, text):\r\n        \"\"\"Extract meaningful tokens from text.\"\"\"\r\n        # Split on whitespace and punctuation, lowercase\r\n        words = re.findall(r'\\b[a-zA-Z_][a-zA-Z0-9_]+\\b', text.lower())\r\n        # Filter very short tokens\r\n        return [w for w in words if len(w) > 2]\r\n    \r\n    def classify_tokens(self):\r\n        \"\"\"Classify tokens as invariant (>1 occurrence) or variant (=1).\"\"\"\r\n        for token, freq in self.token_frequency.items():\r\n            if freq > 1:\r\n                self.invariant_tokens.add(token)\r\n            else:\r\n                self.variant_tokens.add(token)\r\n        \r\n        inv_count = len(self.invariant_tokens)\r\n        var_count = len(self.variant_tokens)\r\n        total = inv_count + var_count\r\n        inv_ratio = inv_count / total if total > 0 else 0\r\n        return {\"invariant\": inv_count, \"variant\": var_count, \"ratio\": inv_ratio}\r\n    \r\n    def predict_next_pulse(self, pulse_idx, n_tokens=20):\r\n        \"\"\"\r\n        Predict next pulse content from current pulse invariants.\r\n        Returns: (predicted_invariants, actual_invariants, accuracy)\r\n        \"\"\"\r\n        if pulse_idx >= len(self.pulses) - 1:\r\n            return None, None, None\r\n        \r\n        current_pulse = self.pulses[pulse_idx][1]\r\n        next_pulse = self.pulses[pulse_idx + 1][1]\r\n        \r\n        # Predict: invariants in current pulse that continue in next pulse\r\n        current_invariants = set(current_pulse) & self.invariant_tokens\r\n        next_invariants = set(next_pulse) & self.invariant_tokens\r\n        \r\n        # Prediction: next invariants = current invariants (persistence assumption)\r\n        predicted = current_invariants\r\n        actual = next_invariants\r\n        \r\n        # Accuracy: how many predicted appear in actual\r\n        if len(predicted) == 0:\r\n            pred_acc = 0.0\r\n        else:\r\n            hits = len(predicted & actual)\r\n            pred_acc = hits / len(predicted)\r\n        \r\n        return predicted, actual, pred_acc\r\n    \r\n    def run_experiment(self, min_pulses=5):\r\n        \"\"\"Run full TIC experiment on pulse logs.\"\"\"\r\n        self.load_pulses()\r\n        \r\n        if len(self.pulses) < min_pulses:\r\n            return {\"error\": f\"Need >= {min_pulses} pulses, found {len(self.pulses)}\"}\r\n        \r\n        # Phase 1: Classification\r\n        classification = self.classify_tokens()\r\n        \r\n        # Phase 2: Prediction\r\n        predictions = []\r\n        for i in range(len(self.pulses) - 1):\r\n            pred, actual, acc = self.predict_next\n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 1\n- Completed at: 2026-03-23 23:49:37\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774324706958}}
